sequenceDiagram
  participant Ctl as Controller tick
  participant C as Channel domain
  participant HW as HV hardware

  Note over C: operating_mode = Automatic<br/>recovery_policy_mode = AUTO_RETRY (or AUTO_DERATE_RETRY)

  Ctl->>C: consume_current(raw)
  C->>C: tick_current_protection() trips
  C->>C: active_fault_cause |= CURRENT
  C->>HW: apply protection action
  Note over C: state = FaultLatched

  Ctl->>C: tick_recovery() (same tick, right after)
  Note over C: mode Automatic + policy allows + not ramping<br/>-> arm cooldown, state = RetryCooldown

  loop each tick while cooldown_remaining_ms > 0
    Ctl->>C: tick_recovery()
    C->>C: cooldown_remaining_ms -= dt_ms
  end

  Note over C: cooldown elapsed

  loop each tick until safe
    Ctl->>C: tick_recovery()
    C->>C: is_safe_to_clear_active()?
    alt still unsafe
      C->>C: stay in RetryCooldown, re-check next tick
    end
  end

  Note over C: measured_current now within safe band

  C->>C: count_active_retries() in sliding window
  alt retries remain (< auto_retry_max_count)
    C->>C: record_retry_attempt()
    C->>C: target = configured_target_voltage<br/>(or derated, for AUTO_DERATE_RETRY)
    C->>C: active_fault_cause = 0, recovering = true
    C->>HW: output re-enabled
    Note over C: state = Ramping
    loop tick_ramp() each tick
      Ctl->>C: tick_ramp() steps operational_target_voltage
    end
    C->>C: target reached -> recovering = false
    Note over C: state = EnabledHolding
  else max retries exhausted, or derated target <= 0
    C->>C: active_fault_cause |= RETRY_EXHAUST
    Note over C: state = FaultLatched (stays,<br/>manual clear now required)
  end
